'''Adil Boulbina''' ({{langx|ar|عادل بولبينة}}; born May 2, 2003) is an Algerian professional footballer who plays for [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Al Duhail ===
On 14 June 2025, Boulbina, the top scorer of the [[2024–25 Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1|2024–25 Algerian Ligue 1 season]], flew to Doha to finalize his transfer to [[Al Duhail SC|Al Duhail]]. Boulbina was accompanied by Sofiane Zetchi, son of [[Paradou AC]] president [[Kheiredine Zetchi]]. The contract, set to last five years, is expected to be signed on 16 June 2025, following the mandatory medical examinations. The transfer fee is estimated at over €4 million, which would mark a record for a player transferred from the Algerian league, surpassing [[Hicham Boudaoui]]’s move to [[OGC Nice]] in 2019. A clause also guarantees 25% of any future transfer fee to [[Paradou AC|Paradou]]. He reportedly turned down offers from other clubs, such as [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] and [[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]], considering Al Duhail’s offer to be more beneficial both sportingly and financially.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.footafrique.com/boulbina-sest-envole-pour-doha-signature-ce-lundi-a-al-duhail-sc/ |title=ALG : Boulbina à Doha, signature ce lundi à Al-Duhail SC (Exclusif) |website=Foot Afrique |date=June 15, 2025 |access-date=June 15, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/verts-deurope/mercato-cest-confirme-boulbina-en-route-pour-le-qatar-280667.html |title=Mercato : C'est confirmé, Boulbina en route pour le Qatar ! |website=DZfoot |date=June 14, 2025 |access-date=June 15, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/transfert-de-boulbina-hicham-boudaoui-supplante/ |title=Transfert de Boulbina : Hicham Boudaoui supplanté ? |website=La Gazette du Fennec |date=June 14, 2025 |access-date=June 15, 2025}}</ref>

On 19 June 2025, Boulbina has signed a 5 year deal with [[Al-Duhail SC]], despite European interest. The move was reportedly facilitated by coach [[Djamel Belmadi]], who promised a 1 or 2 season stint before a transfer to [[S.C. Braga|Braga]], a club linked to Al Duhail’s Qatari investors. The long contract helps the Qatari club protect its investment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/adil-boulbina-a-al-duhail-un-detail-interpelle/ |title=Adil Boulbina à Al Duhail : un détail interpelle ? |website=La Gazette du Fennec |date=June 19, 2025 |access-date=June 20, 2025}}</ref> On 24 November 2025, he scored a hat-trick in the [[2025–26 AFC Champions League Elite league stage|2025–26 AFC Champions League Elite]] helping his team to a 4–2 win over Saudi club [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al Ittihad]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.saudigazette.com.sa/article/656840/Sports/Boulbina-hat-trick-powers-Al-Duhail-to-4-2-win-over-Al-Ittihad-in-AFC-Champions-League-Elite |title=Boulbina hat-trick sinks Al Ittihad as Al Duhail claim 4-2 ACL Elite win |publisher=Saudi Gazette |date=25 November 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Adil Boulbina has been called up by coach [[Madjid Bougherra]] to join the [[Algeria A' national football team]]. Boulbina participate in the preparatory training camp ahead of the friendly match against [[Rwanda national football team|Rwanda]], scheduled for June 9, 2025, at [[Mustapha Tchaker Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.faf.dz/selection-nationale-a-la-liste-de-bougherra-pour-le-match-amical-face-au-rwanda/ |title=SÉLECTION NATIONALE A' : LA LISTE DE BOUGHERRA POUR LE MATCH AMICAL FACE AU RWANDA |website=[[Algerian Football Federation|FAF]] |date=1 June 2025 |access-date=1 June 2025}}</ref> Boulbina stood out by scoring the opening goal of the match, confirming his good form with the local national team. A regular call-up for the Algeria A' squad, Boulbina is considered one of the promising talents of Algerian football.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/en-a-victoire-convaincante-de-lequipe-nationale-a-face-au-rwanda-2-0/ |title=Amical : Victoire convaincante de l'Équipe Nationale A' face au Rwanda (2-0) |website=La Gazette du Fennec |date=9 June 2025 |access-date=19 June 2025}}</ref> In November 2025, he was called up to the national team for the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aps.dz/fr/sports/sport-collectif/mibs0sgu-bougherra-retient-23-joueurs-pour-le-rendez-vous-de-doha|title=Bougherra retient 23 joueurs pour le rendez-vous de Doha|publisher=Algeria Press Service|date=23 November 2025|access-date=25 November 2025}}</ref>

In December 2025, he was named in the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian]] squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Blow for Algeria as key midfielder ruled out of Cup of Nations |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/blow-algeria-key-midfielder-ruled-out-cup-nations-2025-12-19/ |publisher=Reuters |access-date=24 December 2025 |date=19 December 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 January 2026, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 win after extra time over [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] in the round of 16 of the African competition.<ref>{{cite web |last=Williams |first=Ian |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cvg5ln7z2z9t |title=Algeria 1–0 Congo DR |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 January 2026 }}</ref>

